id: pm-vhdc
title: Validate UUID fields at telemetry ingestion boundary
description: Remote telemetry worker logs repeatedly show worker_insert_failed invalid input syntax for type uuid when events contain non-UUID installation_id/session_id/event_id values. Invalid payloads should be rejected (or sanitized/quarantined) before queue insert to prevent retry churn and queue pollution.
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[4]: observability,pm-cli,telemetry,validation
created_at: "2026-04-26T08:38:49.149Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T13:16:13.950Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: Ingestion path validates UUID-typed identifiers before queueing; invalid payloads are dropped/quarantined with explicit counters and do not repeatedly fail worker inserts.
parent: pm-lnq3
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
